but I'm absolutely stunned.

15:39.021 --> 15:41.473
Your grapes are,
how you say, sour?

15:41.473 --> 15:43.391
Listen, you won't believe
what just happened.

15:43.392 --> 15:44.893
Hey, where's my drink?
Oh, I didn't make it.

15:44.893 --> 15:46.394
I've been
on the phone.

15:46.395 --> 15:48.897
It was my old roommate
from Georgetown just called.

15:48.897 --> 15:50.398
Oh, Alan, um,
what's-his-name?

15:50.399 --> 15:52.901
McCarthy. He's up here
from Washington.

15:52.901 --> 15:53.902
On business or something.

15:53.902 --> 15:55.403
And he's on
his way over here.

15:55.404 --> 15:57.906
Well, I hope he knows
the lyrics to "Happy Birthday."

15:57.906 --> 15:59.908
Listen, asshole,
what am I gonna do?

15:59.908 --> 16:00.909
He's straight.

16:00.909 --> 16:02.744
Square City.

16:02.745 --> 16:04.580
I mean, he's really terribly proper.

16:04.580 --> 16:06.081
Awfully good family.

16:06.081 --> 16:08.083
Oh, that's <i>so</i> important.

16:08.083 --> 16:10.802
I mean, his family looks down on people in the theater.

16:10.803 --> 16:11.887
So, what do you think
he'll feel about

16:11.887 --> 16:13.889
this freak show I've got
booked in for dinner?

16:13.889 --> 16:15.891
Oh, Christ,
is that good.

16:15.891 --> 16:17.392
He really lost his spring
on the telephone.

16:17.393 --> 16:20.396
He started crying. And
that's not his style at all.

16:20.396 --> 16:22.898
